CAPE TOWN – South African Police Service officers have arrested five people and seized abalone and processing equipment worth about R3.5-million rand in Mfuleni, Cape Town, Western Cape police said on Saturday.
	
	In the early hours of Saturday morning, members of the provincial tactical response team acted on information about an alleged abalone processing facility at a house in Mfuleni, the SAPS said in a statement. READ: Abalone seized after high-speed sea chase Upon their arrival at the address in Pelican Walk, Sunbird Park, they found abalone to the estimated street value of R3.5 million, which included the equipment used by the suspects. Five suspects aged between 18 and 53 were arrested.They were expected to appear in the Blue Downs Magistrate’s Court once charges had been laid. African News Agency